TITLE: Windowing (Blake)

<li>truncates an infinte series in the time domain
<li>disadvantage
  <ul>
  <li>introduces ripple in the frequency domain
  </ul>
<li>solution:
  <ul>
  <li>apply a non rectangular filter
  <li>advantage
    <ul>
    <li>attenuates the ripple
    </ul>
  <li>disavantage
    <ul>
    <li>broadens the spectral peak
    </ul>
  </ul>
<li>several different algorithms have been provided
  <ul>
  <li>Rectangular
  <li>Hanning
  <li>Hamming
  <li>Blackman
  <li>Dolph-Chebyshev
  </ul>
<li>prudent selection can attenuate the FD ripples
